fields.directions:
The Setup:
  • Start with eyes directly under the bar
  • Grip the bar with a full grip (thumb over fingers)
  • Build a platform by creating an arch in the upper back
The Rep:
  • Bar moves towards sternum, pause then drive

The Setup:
  • Front rack position with bar across shoulders
  • Elbows pointing forward
  • Full grip on bar
  • Feet shoulder width apart, even pressure throughout
  • Breathe in from the abdomen and brace before beginning rep
The Rep
  • Descend backwards then down

The Setup:
  • Grip the bar with a hook grip (thumb under the fingers)
  • Looking straight ahead
  • Bar Starts above the knee
  • Shoulders over the bar
The Rep:
  1. Jump down under the bar by moving the feet
  2. High elbow, fast turn-over with strong lock out
  3. Strong leg drive into a fully extended position

The Setup:
  • High bar position across the shoulders
  • Full Grip (thumb over fingers) with elbows pointing back
  • Feet shoulder width apart with even pressure throughout
  • Breathe in from the abdomen and brace
The Rep:
  • Descend backwards then down
  • Lower until the hips pass the knees

The Setup:
  • Sumo Stance, upright position
  • Barbell set in the landmine position
  • Breathe in from the abdomen and brace
The Rep:
  • Lateral Shift
  • Ensure the knee comes over the toe at the bottom of the rep

The Setup:
  • Position Ball of the foot directly under the barbell
  • Grip the bar just outside of Shoulder width
  • Neutral spine position
  • Externally rotate shoulders to create tension
The Rep:
  • Pull bar towards the stomach without any change in spinal position
  • Ensure the bar touches the floor between each rep

The Setup:
  • Extend the knee and hip to the starting point
  • External rotation of the shoulders to maintain tension
The Rep:
  • Hip-dominant movement pattern
  • Descend by sending hips back, maintaining a strong spinal position

The Setup:
  • Front rack position, bar across shoulders
  • Elbows pointing forward
  • Breathe and brace
The Rep:
  • Descend down until the hip goes past the knee
  • Strong drive out of the bottom of the rep, then accelerate through the last third of the movement

The Setup:
  • Hook Grip (Thumb under fingers)
  • Bar starts just above knee
  • Look straight ahead
  • Sit back into the position
The Rep:
  1. Jump down under the bar by moving the feet
  2. Catch in the front rack position
  3. Strong drive into the fully extended position

Equipment:
  • Resistance band
  • Barbell
  • Ab mat
The Setup:
  • Place both arms inside the band
  • Both ankles between ab mat and barbell
  • Breathe and brace
The Rep:
  • Maintain braced position coming forward
  • Use hamstrings to return to starting position

The Setup:
  • Slight round in the upper back
  • Full weight on the roller
The Rep:
  • Roll to full extension
  • Maintain body position and core engagement throughout

The Setup:
  • Place one side of band under feet
  • stand in neutral position, other side of band held in each hand at side
The Rep:
  • Engage midline
  • Reach up to the sky to fully extend the shoulder. Challenge it but stay in control
  • Maintain a straight arm throughout

The Setup:
  • Barbell rests across hips
  • Feet in narrow stance
  • Shoulders above bench 
The Rep:
  • Squeeze glutes and push hips through
  • Maintain engagement and do not over-extend at the top of the movement
  • Think about keeping your ribs down and make sure you drive to a full extension

The setup:
  • Barbell in the landmine position
  • Set a neutral spine angle
The Rep:
  1. Leg drive to the chest 
  2. Dip an drive overhead

The Setup:
  • Feet shoulder width apart
The Rep:
  • Rotate ball around the head
  • Use torque across the torso to accelerate into the slam
  • Let the hips and ankles move freely in an active stance

The Setup:
  • Externally rotate the shoulders
  • Hands just wide of the shoulders
The Rep:
  • Chest to floor
  • perform squat thrust just before locking out at the top of the press up
  • Remember to maintain this solid position throughout the movement!

The Setup:
  • Bar Across Shoulders
  • Elbows pointing forwards
The Rep:
  • Hips down, knees track forward
  • push knuckles to the ceiling when driving up through the legs
  • Use strong leg extension to drive the hip through into a full lockout!

The Setup:
  • Sit on the floor
  • legs out in front
  • hands by your sides
The Rep:
  • Fully mobilise the spine
  • Hands wide for support
  • Legs fall out wide
  • Reach hands past the heels

The Setup:
  • Full grip on the bar
  • Hang from the bar in a relaxed/dead hang
The Rep:
  • Fully contract shoulder blades
  • Then, relax in to a dead hang

The Setup:
  • Feet positioned in a narrow stance
The Rep:
  • Knee tracks forward
  • Foot maintains full contact with the floor
  • Upright torso
  • Return to starting position between each rep

The Setup:
  • Push support knee into the ground to create tension
The Rep:
  • "Fix a short band around both knees to increase the resistance of the movement. Keep that core tight!"

The Setup:
  • "Kick" DB's into lockout position
The Rep:
  • "Keep a solid neutral spine position throughout and remember to keep that core braced!"

The Setup:
  • bar starts just above the knee
The Rep:
  • "Use and aggressive hip and knee extension, while keeping the bar close to the body to drive into that final high pull position!"

The setup:
  • Barbell placed high on shoulders
  • Initiate breathing sequence
The Rep:
  • Remember to drive through the heel of the extending leg into your full lockout position

The setup:
  • Feet placed either side of the ball
The Rep:
  1. First Section:
    • Strong spinal position
    • Lift the ball to the cradle position
  2. Second Section:
    • "Use a strong knee extension and hip drive to send the ball to the shoulder. Keep the ball close to your body at all times!"

The Rep:
  • The Key is in the rhythm! Chain each part of the movement together, make sure you get your chest to the floor and remember to see the bar before you jump into the pullup"

The Setup:
  • When lying back, secure hands to the bench above head
  • maintain a hollow position
The Rep:
  • "Think about pulling your legs backwards and then up to help get that full extension!"

The Setup:
  • have the band running under both feet and resting in the hands around rib height.
The Rep:
  • "Keep an active stance throughout the movement. Remember to send the leg out diagonally and keep the hips square!"

The Setup:
  • Step into position
The Rep:
  • "Begin with a backwards pull, keeping a strong spinal position. Extend both the hip and knee with force to drive into a full lockout!"

The Setup:
  • Active hands
The Rep:
  • "Focus on the head traveling forwards, in front of the hands. Remember to breathe!"
